HEADWORD: Dichromate
<hw>Di*chro"mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A salt of chromic acid containing two equivalents of the acid
radical to one of the base; -- called also
<altname>bichromate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dichromatic</ent>⟦br⟧
